大陆和非洲的人们正在一系列<a href="https://www.vox.com/world-politics/2024/1/25/24049551/war-increasing-ukraine-gaza-sudan-ethiopia">激烈的战争</a>中战斗和死亡。但是，即使世界变得越来越黑，我<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/the-new-1970s">仍然会感觉到</a>一些绿色拍摄开始在美国社会的地面上戳出头顶。 2010年代的破裂尚未修补，但是人们开始尝试修复问题。</p><p>只是一个小例子：去年，乡村音乐歌手卢克·科姆斯（Luke Combs） <a href="https://variety.com/2023/music/news/luke-combs-fast-car-hitmakers-tracy-chapman-crossover-1235813084/">发行了特雷西·查普曼（Tracy Chapman）1988年的歌曲“ Fast Car”的封面</a>。一些作家和社交媒体摇摇欲坠<a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/arts-entertainment/2023/07/13/tracy-chapman-luke-combs-fast-car-cover/">试图使梳子的封面问题提出问题</a>。但是查普曼（Chapman）近年来几乎从未在公开场合演出过，他指出了半退休并在格莱美奖中<a href="https://people.com/grammys-2024-tracy-chapman-fast-car-no-1-following-luke-combs-duet-8559354">唱着“快车”的二重奏</a>。您可以<a href="https://www.grammy.com/videos/tracy-chapman-luke-combs-fast-car-2024-grammys-performance-66th-annual-grammy-awards">在此处观看演出的视频</a>。这是一个很小的迹象表明，美国人可能开始反对2010年代的膝盖分裂思想。</p><p>因此，无论如何，当今综述的主题是“社会康复的小迹象”。但是首先，播客！这是Econ 102的一集，与Erik Torenberg和特别的来宾Eli Dourado。我和我辩论我们是否应该对技术的未来保持乐观，事实证明我比他更乐观！ </p><iframe class="spotify-wrap podcast" data-attrs="{&quot;image&quot;:&quot;https://i.scdn.co/image/ab6765630000ba8ac9ab643165b3c99e2b571a68&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;E29: Is the Great Stagnation Over?&quot;,&quot;subtitle&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith, Erik Torenberg&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Episode&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://open.spotify.com/episode/4uAwVnTaSDixCEJqLay7HX&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;noScroll&quot;:false}" src="https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/4uAwVnTaSDixCEJqLay7HX" frameborder="0" gesture="media" allowfullscreen="true" allow="encrypted-media" data-component-name="Spotify2ToDOM"></iframe><p>这是<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/no/podcast/econ-102-with-noah-smith-and-erik-torenberg/id1696419056">Apple播客</a>和<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/no/podcast/econ-102-with-noah-smith-and-erik-torenberg/id1696419056">YouTube</a>链接。</p><p>我还出现在丹·舒尔茨（Dan Schulz）的播客“底色”上。我们谈到了各种各样的主题： </p><div id="youtube2-7wi1ZWbZBOc" class="youtube-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;videoId&quot;:&quot;7wi1ZWbZBOc&quot;,&quot;startTime&quot;:null,&quot;endTime&quot;:null}" data-component-name="Youtube2ToDOM"><div class="youtube-inner"><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/7wi1ZWbZBOc?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" gesture="media" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowautoplay="true" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409"></iframe></div></div><p>这是<a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/undertone/id1693303954?i=1000643514905">Apple播客</a>和<a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/3gySmZWDXINAwJuraZM2Bg?si=077c34edf7954a92&amp;nd=1&amp;dlsi=8939b19e6c0a4fa0">Spotify</a>链接。</p><p>无论如何，在本周的有趣事物列表中：</p><h4> 1.使美国再次正常</h4><p>乌克兰战争开始后不久，我写了一篇文章，讲述了美国左右之间如何支持俄罗斯事业的激进分子，因为他们希望美国领导的世界秩序的不稳定能够帮助他们在美国范围内获得权力： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;f20512ff-916a-413d-910c-b90c2f1252f9&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;In the first couple of weeks after Vladimir Putin ordered his legions into Ukraine, the media narrative was overwhelmed by the moral clarity of the situation. A totalitarian tyrant had launched a murderous, unprovoked invasion of another country, whose people were valiantly fighting to defend themselves. America&#8217;s hyper-partisan shouters, if not exactly&#8230;&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Putin's war and the Chaos Climbers&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2022-03-21T08:50:26.382Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substack